TY  - JOUR
AU  - Burkart, Mike
AU  - Miglietta, Salvatore
AU  - Ostergaard, Charlotte
T1  - Why Do Boards Exist? Governance Design in the Absence of Corporate Law
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhac072
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 36
IS  - 5
SP  - 1788
EP  - 1836
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study under which circumstances firms choose to install boards and their roles in a historical setting in which neither boards nor their duties are mandated by law. Boards arise in firms with large, heterogeneous shareholder bases. We propose that an important role of boards is to mediate between heterogeneous shareholders with divergent interests. Voting restrictions are common and ensure that boards are representative and not captured by large blockholders. Boards are given significant powers to both mediate and monitor management, and these roles are intrinsically linked.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhac072
ER  - 



